d on the Upper Level.\r\n<h4>ANIMALS</h4>\r\nOnly service animals are permitted on the Lynnwood Convention Center premises. Pets are not allowed.\r\n<h4>ATM</h4>\r\nThe Lynnwood Convention Center does not have an ATM on the premises. There are several bank/ATMs within walking distance of the building.\r\n<h4>CHARGING STATIONS</h4>\r\nComplementary charging stations can be found throughout the building on both the upper and lower levels at the provided workstations and soft furniture groupings.\r\n<h4>FIRST AID</h4>\r\nThere is a first aid kit on the Upper and Lower Levels of the building. If you are in need of first aid, ask a Lynnwood Convention Center Staff Member for assistance. If you are experiencing a medical emergency, call 9-1-1.\r\n<h4>EMERGENCY EXITS/ MUSTER POINTS</h4>\r\nThere are many emergency exits throughout the building. Emergency Procedures are available in print at the front Desk. In case of an emergency, follow the exits to one of the three muster points outside of the building and wait for the emergency professionals to arrive. The three muster points are: the corner of 196th Street and 36th Ave, the corner of 36th Ave and 195th Place, and northwest corner of the building courtyard.\r\n<h4>MOTHER’S ROOM</h4>\r\nThe Lynnwood Convention Center provides a lounge area for new mothers. The mother\'s room provides an optional, secluded room for mothers needing to pump or feed their child while attending a conference or event in the building. The private space, located off the lower level women\'s restroom, includes comfortable chairs, side tables and electrical outlets.\r\n<h4>PARKING</h4>\r\nThe Lynnwood Convention Plaza can accommodate 400 parking spaces. For large events there maybe overflow parking at an off-site location. Visit our Directions &amp; Parking page for details.\r\n<h4>RECYCLING/ SUSTAINABILITY</h4>\r\nRecycling is part of the Lynnwood Convention Center’s operating philosophy. The Lynnwood Convention Center recycles paper, cardboard, plastic, cans, bottles, wood pallets and more. Recycle containers are also made available throughout the facility. The Lynnwood Convention Center has adopted a composting system that helps reduce waste from our kitchen (we use 100% compostable items at our coffee stations).\r\n<h4>RESTAURANTS</h4>\r\nThere are dozens of restaurants within walking and driving distance of the Lynnwood Convention Center.\r\n<h4>SECURITY</h4>\r\nThe Convention Center premises is under video surveillance including meeting rooms, concourses and the parking lot.\r\n<h4>SMOKING / NON-SMOKING POLICY</h4>\r\nThe Lynnwood Convention Center is a non-smoking facility. Smoking is not permitted within the facility or within twenty-five (25) feet of any exterior entrance door. This policy applies to any vapor type cigarettes. Smoking is allowed only in designated smoking areas.\r\n<h4>WI-FI</h4>\r\nThe Lynnwood Convention Center has complementary Wi-Fi for guests. Our public Wi-Fi network is “LCC Free” and does not require a username or password. This Wi-Fi is available to all guests in the building so connection speed cannot be guaranteed and may vary throughout the day.','Lynnwood Convention Center','','publish','closed','closed','','lynnwood-convention-center','','','2019-01-27 21:28:39','2019-01-27 21:28:39','',0,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/?post_type=locations&#038;p=28',0,'locations','',0),(31,1,'2018-05-25 18:04:05','2018-05-25 18:04:05','Welcome to the PNW Mouse Meet! Explore and check out some past events. We are always hard at work planning for next year so check back soon!','PNW Mouse Meets','','publish','closed','closed','','pnw-mouse-meets','','','2019-02-24 19:22:13','2019-02-24 19:22:13','',0,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/?page_id=31',0,'page','',0),(32,1,'2018-05-25 18:04:05','2018-05-25 18:04:05','','PNW Mouse Meets','','inherit','closed','closed','','31-revision-v1','','','2018-05-25 18:04:05','2018-05-25 18:04:05','',31,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/31-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(33,