ood Convention Center does not have an ATM on the premises. There are several bank/ATMs within walking distance of the building.\nCHARGING STATIONS Complementary charging stations can be found throughout the building on both the upper and lower levels at the provided workstations and soft furniture groupings.\nFIRST AID There is a first aid kit on the Upper and Lower Levels of the building. If you are in need of first aid, ask a Lynnwood Convention Center Staff Member for assistance. If you are experiencing a medical emergency, call 9-1-1.\nEMERGENCY EXITS/ MUSTER POINTS There are many emergency exits throughout the building. Emergency Procedures are available in print at the front Desk. In case of an emergency, follow the exits to one of the three muster points outside of the building and wait for the emergency professionals to arrive. The three muster points are: the corner of 196th Street and 36th Ave, the corner of 36th Ave and 195th Place, and northwest corner of the building courtyard.\nMOTHER’S ROOM The Lynnwood Convention Center provides a lounge area for new mothers. The mother\'s room provides an optional, secluded room for mothers needing to pump or feed their child while attending a conference or event in the building. The private space, located off the lower level women\'s restroom, includes comfortable chairs, side tables and electrical outlets.\nPARKING The Lynnwood Convention Plaza can accommodate 400 parking spaces. For large events there maybe overflow parking at an off-site location. Visit our Directions &amp; Parking page for details.\nRECYCLING/ SUSTAINABILITY Recycling is part of the Lynnwood Convention Center’s operating philosophy. The Lynnwood Convention Center recycles paper, cardboard, plastic, cans, bottles, wood pallets and more. Recycle containers are also made available throughout the facility. The Lynnwood Convention Center has adopted a composting system that helps reduce waste from our kitchen (we use 100% compostable items at our coffee stations).\nRESTAURANTS There are dozens of restaurants within walking and driving distance of the Lynnwood Convention Center.\nSECURITY The Convention Center premises is under video surveillance including meeting rooms, concourses and the parking lot.\nSMOKING / NON-SMOKING POLICY The Lynnwood Convention Center is a non-smoking facility. Smoking is not permitted within the facility or within twenty-five (25) feet of any exterior entrance door. This policy applies to any vapor type cigarettes. Smoking is allowed only in designated smoking areas.\nWI-FI The Lynnwood Convention Center has complementary Wi-Fi for guests. Our public Wi-Fi network is “LCC Free” and does not require a username or password. This Wi-Fi is available to all guests in the building so connection speed cannot be guaranteed and may vary throughout the day.</h4>','Lynnwood Convention Center','','inherit','closed','closed','','28-autosave-v1','','','2018-05-31 20:00:56','2018-05-31 20:00:56','',28,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/28-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(159,1,'2018-05-31 21:46:24','2018-05-31 21:46:24','','Home Page','','inherit','closed','closed','','22-revision-v1','','','2018-05-31 21:46:24','2018-05-31 21:46:24','',22,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/22-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(160,1,'2018-05-31 21:56:59','2018-05-31 21:56:59','','Home Page','','inherit','closed','closed','','22-revision-v1','','','2018-05-31 21:56:59','2018-05-31 21:56:59','',22,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/22-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(161,1,'2018-06-06 05:08:50','2018-06-06 05:08:50','<div id=\"wsb-element-3bb85533-e9db-4d83-9dc8-47bff2cd65d0\" class=\"wsb-element-text\" data-type=\"element\">\r\n<div class=\"txt \"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"wsb-element-399ae084-d95e-4a76-9412-0b5ec4b163fd\" class=\"wsb-element-text\" data-type=\"element\">\r\n<div class=\"txt \">\r\n<h2>About the Events</h2>\r\nThe PNW Mouse Meet is an unofficial Disney Fan Event that was created by Disney Fans FOR Disney Fans. This annual event provides Disney enthusiasts the opportunity to get together right here in the Pacific Northwest to share and celebrate all things Disney.\r\n\r\nThe PNW Mouse Meet is comprised of a variety of experiences including:\r\nDisney Celebrities, Disney podcasters, authors, and travel experts, Disneyana Collectibles Vendors, Disney Fan Collection Displays, Pin Trading, Trivia, Food, magical surprises, fantastic auction items with proceeds going to charity, Disney Fans meeting fellow Disney Fans, A little magic, a little pixie dust and so much more.\r\n\r\nThe inaugural PNW Mouse Meet event took place on Saturday August 15, 2009 at the Lynnwood Convention Center and has grown from 150 Guests to over 400 Guests today.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2>Our PNW Mouse Meet Team:</h2>\r\n<div class=\"flex-container\">\r\n<div class=\"col\" style=\"flex-grow: 2;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-428\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px;\" src=\"https://pnwmousemeet.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/cf0bfea9f2c56fbbe32846cf6e6dd886.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"223\" height=\"242\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"col\" style=\"flex-grow: 2;\">\r\n<h3>Don Morin</h3>\r\n<h4>Founder/Host</h4>\r\nSince 2009 Don and his team have been creating a magical experience for thousands of Guests.\r\n\"Passion, Disney Fandom and giving them more than they expect are key ingredients to our success!\"\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"flex-container\">\r\n<div class=\"col\" style=\"flex-grow: 2;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-429\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px;\" src=\"https://pnwmousemeet.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/1eb0bf4be885c7332a88b09abc007fb8.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"214\" height=\"186\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"col\" style=\"flex-grow: 2;\">\r\n<h3>PNW Mouse Meet Volunteer Team</h3>\r\n<h4>An amazing group of individuals who LOVE making Magic for our Guests.</h4>\r\nWe appreciate all of their time, efforts and excitement!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','About Us','','publish','closed','closed','','about-us','','','2019-02-28 01:04:29','2019-02-28 01:04:29','',0,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/?page_id=161',0,'page','',0),(162,1,'2018-06-06 05:08:50','2018-06-06 05:08:50','','About Us','','inherit','closed','closed','','161-revision-v1','','','2018-06-06 05:08:50','2018-06-06 05:08:50','',161,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/161-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(164,1,'2018-06-25 23:36:57','2018-06-25 23:36:57','','PNW Mouse Meet Index Fields','','publish','closed','closed','','acf_pnw-mouse-meet-index-fields','','','2018-06-25 23:47:33','2018-06-25 23:47:33','',0,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/?post_type=acf&#038;p=164',0,'acf','',0),(165,1,'2018-06-25 23:41:18','2018-06-25 23:41:18','','PNW Mouse Meets','','inherit','closed','closed','','31-revision-v1','','','2018-06-25 23:41:18','2018-06-25 23:41:18','',31,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/31-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(166,1,'2018-06-25 23:46:08','2018-06-25 23:46:08','[Best_Wordpress_Gallery id=\"1\" gal_title=\"PNW Mouse Meet Index\"]','PNW Mouse Meet Index','','publish','closed','closed','','pnw-mouse-meet-index','','','2018-06-25 23:46:08','2018-06-25 23:46:08','',0,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/bwg_gallery/pnw-mouse-meet-index/',0,'bwg_gallery','',0),(167,1,'2018-06-25 23:47:53','2018-06-25 23:47:53','','PNW Mouse Meets','','inherit','closed','closed','','31-revision-v1','','','2018-06-25 23:47:53','2018-06-25 23:47:53','',31,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/31-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(168,1,'2018-06-25 23:48:49','2018-06-25 23:48:49','','PNW Mouse Meets','','inherit','closed','closed','','31-revision-v1','','','2018-06-25 23:48:49','2018-06-25 23:48:49','',31,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/31-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(169,1,'2018-06-25 23:49:19','2018-06-25 23:49:19','','PNW Mouse Meets','','inherit','closed','closed','','31-revision-v1','','','2018-06-25 23:49:19','2018-06-25 23:49:19','',31,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/31-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(170,1,'2018-06-25 23:49:36','2018-06-25 23:49:36','','PNW Mouse Meets','','inherit','closed','closed','','31-revision-v1','','','2018-06-25 23:49:36','2018-06-25 23:49:36','',31,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/31-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(171,1,'2018-06-26 00:07:49','2018-06-26 00:07:49','','Mouse Meet Info Item','','publish','closed','closed','','acf_mouse-meet-info-item','','','2018-06-26 00:09:44','2018-06-26 00:09:44','',0,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/?post_type=acf&#038;p=171',0,'acf','',0),(172,1,'2018-06-26 00:20:12','2018-06-26 00:20:12','<h2>COVID-19 Update</h2>\r\nPlease see our <a href=\"/mouse_meet_info_item/covid-protocols/\">COVID-19 Protocols</a> page for the latest updates and information.\r\n\r\n<a class=\"btn btn-primary\" href=\"/mouse_meet_info_item/covid-protocols/\">COVID-19 Information</a>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2>General Rules &amp; Information</h2>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Name badges must be worn at all times while on the premises and during the PNW Mouse Meet event. Name badges and lanyards will be distributed at the event registration table upon check in.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Name badges and tickets are non-transferable.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Reselling, transferring or other unauthorized use of tickets/name badges will be grounds for removal from the event and/or forfeit of the Tickets without compensation.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Inappropriate or disorderly conduct by any attending guest, volunteer or other person will result in actions deemed appropriate by the PNW Mouse Meet LLC Management and may result in expulsion from the event.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">For the consideration of others and in accordance with Washington State law, the PNW MM requests that you refrain from smoking inside the Lynnwood Convention Center and within 25 feet of any entrance.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">We request that you please silence your cell phones, beepers, and other electronic devices during speaker presentations so as to not disturb the show or other guests.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Offensive and/or counterfeit Disneyana may not be worn, displayed, or sold at any time during the PNW Mouse Meet event. The PNW Mouse Meet reserves the right to deem an item not suitable at their discretion. Any violations may result in expulsion from the event. There is absolutely no selling of any items without prior written agreement and permission of the PNW Mouse Meet LLC.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Cell phones, still cameras, and video cameras are welcome in main event areas.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Video Cameras or any other Video and/or Audio Recording devices MUST be turned off during the Guest Speaker Presentations.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">All media representatives MUST check in with an Official PNW Mouse Meet representative upon arrival and announce any recording devices including still and video cameras as well as cell phones, computers, and/or other recording devices. ONLY pre-approved and authorized media are allowed to photograph, video, or otherwise record inside the Lynnwood Convention Center and at the PNW Mouse Meet event.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">By attending the PNW Mouse Meet™ event you may be photographed, videotaped or voice recorded. By purchasing your ticket, all Guests in your party hereby agrees that PNW Mouse Meet LLC and its affiliates may use the guest’s name, likeness, photograph, recorded video and/or recorded voice in connection with the event for any and all purposes including but not limited to: media reporting, promotion, marketing, Event DVD’s, Documentaries for and in connection with the PNW Mouse Meet™.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">By purchasing a ticket, Event Attendee(s) immediately assumes any and all risks and danger incidental to the event for which they are attending, whether occurring prior to, during or after the event. Event attendee shall defend, indemnify, and hold harmless PNW Mouse Meet™ and its parents, affiliates, subsidiaries, licensees, successors and assigns, the facility, participants, participating advertisers, vendors, sponsors, and clients, and the respective owners, officers, directors, agents and employees of each from and against all liability, actions, claims, demands, judgments, penalties, fines, losses, property damage, other injuries.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Disregard of any of these rules may be grounds for removal.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">The PNW Mouse Meet™ is an Unofficial Disney Fan Event. The PNW Mouse Meet™ is not affiliated with the Walt Disney Company or any of its affiliates or subsidiaries. Visit the Official Disney website at www.disney.com</p>','Rules & Information','','publish','closed','closed','','rules-information','','','2022-03-15 04:53:49','2022-03-15 04:53:49','',0,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/?post_type=mouse_meet_info_item&#038;p=172',0,'mouse_meet_info_item','',0),(173,1,'2018-06-26 00:10:09','2018-06-26 00:10:09','','Rules','','inherit','open','closed','','rules','','','2018-06-26 00:10:09','2018-06-26 00:10:09','',172,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Rules.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(174,1,'2018-06-26 04:21:09','2018-06-26 04:21:09','<div id=\"wsb-canvas-template-container\">\r\n<div id=\"wsb-element-1bf5ac62-004b-48a6-818b-0dab5d2a1d63\" class=\"wsb-element-text\" data-type=\"element\">\r\n<div class=\"txt \">\r\n\r\n<span class=\"editor_footer\">Copyright Pacific Northwest Mouse Meet™ LLC. All rights reserved.</span><span class=\"editor_footer\">​\r\nThis website is not part of, endorsed or authorized by, or affiliated with the Walt Disney Company or it\'s affiliates.\r\nVisit the official Disney website at Disney.com </span>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"wsb-element-e7d3f901-259a-475a-93c3-75f26a1fcb44\" class=\"wsb-element-text\" data-type=\"element\">\r\n<div class=\"txt \">\r\n\r\n<strong>When is the PNW Mouse Meet?</strong>\r\nThe PNW Mouse Meet happens each year in the summer! This is a one day event. Please check the <a href=\"/pnw-mouse-meets/\">PNW Mouse Meet</a> Details Page to see more details about the day of event as they become available.\r\n\r\n<strong>Is this event part of the Disney Company?</strong>\r\nNo. This event is in no way affiliated with the Walt Disney Company and/or any of its affiliates. This event has been created by Disney Fans for Disney Fans and is considered an Unofficial Disney Fan Event.\r\n\r\n<strong>How can I get tickets for the event?</strong>\r\nTickets are for sale ONLY on our website. Visit the Event Page for details. Tickets are limited to ensure an intimate experience and Tickets have Sold Out every year. No tickets will be available at the venue.\r\n\r\n<strong>Can I get tickets at the door?</strong>\r\nNO tickets will be available the day of the event or at the door.\r\n\r\n<strong>Are there hotels nearby I can stay at?</strong>\r\nYes. The Embassy Suites Hotel in Lynnwood is once again our official hotel partner. Check out the Official Hotel Link on the PNWMM Event Page. There are also a variety of other Hotel options nearby, just click on the CONVENTION CENTER Info Box on the PNWMM Main Page to learn more.\r\n\r\n<strong>Can I bring my camera or video camera?</strong>\r\nYes. There will be many photo opportunities with Celebrities, Authors, Podcasters, Displays, other Disney Fans and surprises. Photos and video are allowed in all areas of the events space. <strong>There is NO Audio or Video recording allowed </strong>during Guest Speaker Presentations. Photographs are ok.\r\n\r\n<strong>Will it cost for Guest Celebrity Autographs:</strong>\r\nOur Celebrity Guest Speakers will be available for Meet &amp; Greet opportunities. Each Celebrity may have items for sale and/or may charge for autographs. This is up to the individual and is at their own discretion. Ask a PNWMM Team Member for details at the Meet/Greet areas during the event.\r\n\r\n<strong>Will there be food available at the event?</strong>\r\nYes. There will be food items such as pastries, sandwiches, salads, beverages, snacks, treats and more available for purchase at the convention center Café for your convenience. There are also several restaurants nearby and within walking distance. Outside food is not permitted in the event.\r\n\r\n<strong>Can I bring Disney Items to sell at the PNW Mouse Meet?</strong>\r\nYou must be a Registered Vendor in order to sell items at the PNW Mouse Meet event. No other unauthorized selling of items is allowed at the event and may be grounds for removal from the event without ticket refund or compensation. For future Vendor consideration, please email us at vendorinfo@pnwmousemeet.com for more information on how to become a vendor at this event.\r\n\r\n<strong>Can I bring or hand out Business Cards, Information or Advertising at the event?</strong>\r\n\r\nONLY Registered &amp; Paid Vendors are allowed to solicit and sell things to our Guests. No other solicitations of any kind are allowed. Any Guests violating this rule may be asked to leave the event. For future Vendor consideration, please email us at vendorinfo@pnwmousemeet.com for more information on how to become a vendor at this event.\r\n\r\n<strong>Is there an ATM at the Convention Center?</strong>\r\nThere is <strong>NO ATM </strong>at the Convention Center. There are several Banks with ATMs within 4 blocks of the Convention Center.\r\n\r\n<strong>Does PNWMM and/or Vendors accept Credit Card at the event?</strong>\r\nThe PNWMM Booth does accept cash and credit cards. Each Vendor is an individual entity and may or may not accept credit cards however many do. <strong>The Charity Raffle Tickets are Cash Only.</strong> Celebrity fees for autographs or other items for sale may be cash only.\r\n\r\n<strong>Can I Dress Up in Costume for the PNW Mouse Meet?</strong>\r\n\r\nWe welcome Guests who  are Disney Bounding or Cosplay. We do not allow weapons such as knives, swords or other dangerous items. We also do not allow items that LOOK like dangerous weapons. Things like Light Sabers or Thor\'s Hammer is acceptable. We look forward to seeing many amazing Cosplay and Bounding this year!\r\n\r\n<strong>Can I or my company be a Sponsor of the PNW Mouse Meet?</strong>\r\nWe are accepting inquiries and applications for quality businesses that fit our Partner Profile as a Sponsor of future PNW Mouse Meet events. Please email us at sponsorinfo@pnwmousemeet.com or <a href=\"/contact-us\">contact us</a> for more information.\r\n\r\nIf you have a specific question you would like answered regarding the PNW Mouse Meet, please visit the CONTACT US tab at the top of the page to submit your question.\r\n\r\nThank you!\r\nPNW Mouse Meet Team.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<em><strong>The PNW Mouse Meet™ is an Unofficial Disney Fan Event. The PNW Mouse Meet™ is not affiliated with the Walt Disney Company or any of its affiliates or subsidiaries. Visit the Official Disney website at www.disney.com</strong></em>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Frequently Asked Questions','','publish','closed','closed','','frequently-asked-questions','','','2019-02-20 04:54:13','2019-02-20 04:54:13','',0,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/?post_type=mouse_meet_info_item&#038;p=174',0,'mouse_meet_info_item','',0),(175,1,'2018-06-26 04:21:04','2018-06-26 04:21:04','','FAQs','','inherit','open','closed','','faqs','','','2018-06-26 04:21:04','2018-06-26 04:21:04','',174,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/FAQs.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(176,1,'2018-06-26 04:22:54','2018-06-26 04:22:54','<h2>Door Decorating Information</h2>\r\nBy choosing to book a PNW Mouse Meet Group Rate Room at the Embassy Suites in Lynnwood during the weekend of the PNWMM, you can take advantage of ALL the Group Benefits as well as participate in the VERY Popular Room Door &amp; Window Decorating Contest!!\r\n\r\nGuest Room Door &amp; Window Decorating Contest!\r\n<h2>Prizes</h2>\r\nWe will be awarding prizes for the THREE (3) Best Disney Themed Hotel Room Windows.\r\n\r\n<strong>1st Place:</strong>Themed Gift Bag filled with goodies and a $150.00 Disney Gift Card!\r\n<strong>2nd Place:</strong>Themed Gift Bag filled with goodies and a $100.00 Disney Gift Card!\r\n<strong>3rd Place:</strong>Themed Gift Bag with goodies and a $50.00 Disney Gift Card!\r\n\r\nOn Saturday during the main PNWMM event, we will be showing video from all the decorated doors so over 500 Disney Fans will see YOUR decorations!! Prizes will be awarded at that time!!\r\n<h2>Important Information</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Decoration Judging will take place between 9:30pm &amp; 10pm by PNWMM Cast Members.</li>\r\n 	<li>You are welcome to begin decorating as soon as you check in Friday afternoon!</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Room Window dimensions: 43½ inches Wide X 76½ inches Tall</strong></li>\r\n 	<li>Room Door is normal size Door.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<u><strong>NOTE:</strong></u><strong>\r\nThe Windows to each room are now FROSTED and you are Unable to see through the Windows! We highly recommend decorating the OUTSIDE of the Window and Door ONLY.</strong>\r\n\r\n[smartslider3 slider=7]\r\n\r\n<h2>Decoration Rules</h2>\r\n<em><strong>The Hotel has also asked that we pass along the following rules for the decoration contest:</strong></em>\r\n\r\nDecoration should NOT block public walkways, hallways, door entries or railings\r\nGuest occupying room is responsible for all cleanup and disposal of decorations\r\nItems APPROVED to use: Blue Painter’s Tape, Post It Note type sticky back paper, suction cups and other items that will NOT leave a residue or any other markings.\r\nNO nails, thumbtacks, glue, super glue, duct tape or any other item that would leave a mark, hole, scratches, sticky residue or other defects on doors, windows, walls, etc.\r\nEmbassy Suites will hold the Room Guest fully responsible and liable for any damage that may occur.\r\n\r\nWe ask that you be respectful of other guests and the hotel’s rules.\r\nHave a GREAT time decorating and we are SO excited to see what you come up with!!\r\n\r\nIf you should have any questions please contact us a hotel@pnwmousemeet.com','Room Window Decorating Contest','','publish','closed','closed','','room-window-decorating-contest','','','2022-03-02 02:21:25','2022-03-02 02:21:25','',0,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/?post_type=mouse_meet_info_item&#038;p=176',0,'mouse_meet_info_item','',0),(177,1,'2018-06-26 04:21:30','2018-06-26 04:21:30','','present-year','','inherit','open','closed','','present-year','','','2018-06-26 04:21:30','2018-06-26 04:21:30','',176,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/present-year.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(178,1,'2018-06-26 04:24:47','2018-06-26 04:24:47','','Image','','publish','closed','closed','','image','','','2018-06-26 04:24:47','2018-06-26 04:24:47','',0,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/image/',0,'bwg_share','',0),(180,1,'2018-06-26 04:31:45','2018-06-26 04:31:45','<div id=\"wsb-element-f208115d-96e0-4b23-bf96-3786816dd98d\" class=\"wsb-element-text\" data-type=\"element\">\r\n<div class=\"txt \">\r\n\r\nFor 8 years Charita served as Development Manager of the Scenic Illusion team. The Scenic Illusion team was an application and integration team, focused on developing new tools and techniques to supply designers with new and expanded capabilities for storytelling. Under her management, the Scenic Illusion Team was awarded in excess of 20 patents on the company’s behalf.\r\n\r\nShe currently serves as Senior Creative Producer and has delivered attraction projects in the Walt Disney World, Disneyland Resort, and Tokyo portfolios and has lead several special projects such as the Maker Faire Exhibit and Parks and Resort’s D23 Exhibit (a convention for Disney fans).​\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"wsb-element-e5a3af8f-b7d8-4b63-bc58-d17226417206\" class=\"wsb-element-text\" data-type=\"element\">\r\n<div class=\"txt \">\r\n\r\nCharita also received the prestigious <strong><em>Walt Disney Legacy Award </em></strong>for \"Keeping the Magic Alive through exemplary performance and commitment to the traditions and ideals established by Walt Disney\" which also allows her the privilege of wearing a Blue Name Badge.\r\n\r\nOut of the office, Charita serves her community as a facilitator of women\'s ministries, an awarding winning nature photographer, a commercial hand model, and an avid gardener.\r\n\r\n*  *  *  *  *\r\n\r\n​Charita\'s exciting Presentation, entitled, <em><strong>\"Join me in the Sandbox: A Decade of Scenic Illusions\", </strong></em>will take us on a journey behind the scenes in how Charita and her team create new ways, tools and forms of storytelling for Guests in Disney Parks around the world.​\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Charita Carter','','publish','closed','closed','','charita-carter','','','2019-02-19 05:22:33','2019-02-19 05:22:33','',0,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/?post_type=guest_speakers&#038;p=180',0,'guest_speakers','',0),(181,1,'2018-06-26 04:31:11','2018-06-26 04:31:11','','charita','','inherit','open','closed','','charita','','','2018-06-26 04:31:11','2018-06-26 04:31:11','',180,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/charita.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(183,1,'2018-07-12 20:27:42','2018-07-12 20:27:42',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','183','','','2019-02-12 04:12:14','2019-02-12 04:12:14','',0,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/?p=183',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(184,1,'2018-07-13 01:09:38','2018-07-13 01:09:38','','PNWMM 2017-4-X3','','inherit','open','closed','','pnwmm-2017-4-x3','','','2018-07-13 01:09:38','2018-07-13 01:09:38','',31,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/PNWMM-2017-4-X3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(185,1,'2018-07-13 01:45:19','2018-07-13 01:45:19','<div id=\"wsb-element-e0626b8f-37d8-4c70-81a3-3eb81e1dd034\" class=\"wsb-element-image\" data-type=\"element\">\r\n<div class=\"wsb-image-inner \">\r\n<div class=\"img\"><img src=\"http://nebula.wsimg.com/cbdb3cf104c361147da14ca29a3f3cf9?AccessKeyId=E3A6255687A1A4A02BF0&amp;disposition=0&amp;alloworigin=1\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"wsb-element-4a176a18-8589-4d50-b138-fa0cf44ffc8c\" class=\"wsb-element-text\" data-type=\"element\">\r\n<div class=\"txt \">\r\n\r\n<strong>Camille Dixon </strong>is heard in Southern California as the Park Announcer for Disney California Adventure and as a promo voice on PBS SoCal. She is the signature voice for Kroger-owned Smith’s, King Soopers and City Market in the Intermountain West. Camille’s narrations bring vitality and clarity to every endeavor from automotive repair to x-ray technology. Non-broadcast clients include Allergan, Cisco, Hyundai, Liberty Mutual, Raytheon and Toshiba.\r\nOn television, Camille has built a career sharing knowledge and understanding of our world as host of numerous PBS pledge specials. Her work with public broadcasting began as a classical music host on public radio for ten years.  Camille is the host and co-producer of the public television series, ON TOUR: Exploring Creativity and Innovation.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://nebula.wsimg.com/ce10ebb660d10d37f02e4f8086da796b?AccessKeyId=E3A6255687A1A4A02BF0&amp;disposition=0&amp;alloworigin=1\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Bill Rogers </strong>is an American voice actor who has been the Park Announcer for Disneyland since 1991, succeeding Jack Wagner in recording various PA announcements throughout the park.\r\nHe has also done PA announcements for Walt Disney World and the Tokyo Disney Resort as well. His voice can also be heard in It\'s a Small World Holiday as Santa Claus.\r\nVoice over and commercial producer for over forty years, Bill has also voiced everything from automotive to zoos. As a narrator, Bill\'s expertise in medical and scientific terminology keeps him in demand for clients IBM, Boeing, Beckman-Coulter, and Schneider Electric… 75 of the Fortune 100. Bill\'s announcing skills show up at amusement parks in Osaka and Tokyo, Japan... Anaheim, Hollywood, Santa Monica and San Diego on the US West coast, and New York, Richmond, Orlando and Tampa in the East.\r\n\r\n</div>','Bill Rogers and Camille Dixon','','publish','closed','closed','','bill-rogers-and-camille-dixon','','','2019-01-27 00:02:21','2019-01-27 00:02:21','',0,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/?post_type=guest_speakers&#038;p=185',0,'guest_speakers','',0),(186,1,'2018-07-13 01:45:49','2018-07-13 01:45:49','','bill-camille','','inherit','open','closed','','bill-camille','','','2018-07-13 01:45:49','2018-07-13 01:45:49','',185,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/bill-camille.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(187,1,'2018-07-13 04:29:31','2018-07-13 04:29:31','The 2016 PNW Mouse Meet event took place on Saturday July 9th at the Lynnwood Convention Center in Lynnwood Washington. The event day included numerous Interactive Activities, Photo Opps, Disneyana Vendors, Dole Whip, Entertaining Videos, Celebrity Autographs, Podcasters, Travel Professionals, Authors, Charity Raffle Prizes, Attraction Vehicles, Pin Trading, Mickey Rice Krispy Treats, Celebrities, fun, laughs and so much more.','2016','','publish','closed','closed','','2016','','','2019-02-28 01:38:46','2019-02-28 01:38:46','',0,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/?post_type=pnw_mouse_meets&#038;p=187',0,'pnw_mouse_meets','',0),(188,1,'2018-07-13 04:54:38','2018-07-13 04:54:38','The 2015 PNW Mouse Meet took place on Saturday July 11 to rave reviews! Hosting over 400 Guests from 11 states &amp; Canada. Guest Speakers this year were Margaret Kerry (Model for Tinker Bell, Pete Renaday (Voice), Mark Silverman (Voice), Imagineer Joe Herrington and Claire Keane (Animator) and Kristin Rodack &amp; Kevin Kern from D23!\r\n\r\n​An incredible day filled with Disney Fans, Magical Pixie Dust and so much more!','2015','','publish','closed','closed','','2015','','','2019-02-28 01:38:32','2019-02-28 01:38:32','',0,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/?post_type=pnw_mouse_meets&#038;p=188',0,'pnw_mouse_meets','',0),(189,1,'2018-07-13 04:37:41','2018-07-13 04:37:41','Robert Henry \"Bob\" Gurr (born October 25, 1931 in Los Angeles, California) is an American amusement ride designer and Imagineer. His most famous work was for Walt Disney\'s Disneyland Park, and its subsequent sister parks. Gurr is said to have designed most, if not all, of the ride vehicles of the Disneyland attractions, including Autopia, Haunted Mansion, the Disneyland Monorail, the Submarine Voyage, and the Matterhorn Bobsleds. He was named a Disney Legend in 2004. He also worked on the King Kong Encounter animatronic for Universal Studios Hollywood.','Bob Gurr','','publish','closed','closed','','bob-gurr','','','2019-02-21 16:28:06','2019-02-21 16:28:06','',0,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/?post_type=guest_speakers&#038;p=189',0,'guest_speakers','',0),(190,1,'2018-07-13 04:35:48','2018-07-13 04:35:48','','bob-gurr','','inherit','open','closed','','speakers-2016','','','2018-07-13 04:36:47','2018-07-13 04:36:47','',189,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/speakers-2016.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(191,1,'2018-07-13 04:40:01','2018-07-13 04:40:01','<b>Martin A. \"Marty\" Sklar</b> (February 6, 1934 – July 27, 2017) was a scriptwriter and construction developer. He was <a title=\"The Walt Disney Company\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Walt_Disney_Company\">The Walt Disney Company</a>\'s international ambassador for <a title=\"Walt Disney Imagineering\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Walt_Disney_Imagineering\">Walt Disney Imagineering</a>, the <a title=\"Subsidiary\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Subsidiary\">subsidiary</a> of the company which designs and constructs <a title=\"Walt Disney Parks and Resorts\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Walt_Disney_Parks_and_Resorts\">Disney theme parks and resorts</a> across the world. He was formerly vice president of Concepts and Planning for the company, before being promoted to president, then vice chairman and principal creative executive before his final role. Disney honored him with a <a title=\"Disneyland\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disneyland\">Disneyland</a> window dedication ceremony on his date of retirement, July 17, 2009.','Marty Sklar','','publish','closed','closed','','marty-sklar','','','2018-07-13 04:40:01','2018-07-13 04:40:01','',0,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/?post_type=guest_speakers&#038;p=191',0,'guest_speakers','',0),(192,1,'2018-07-13 04:39:37','2018-07-13 04:39:37','','marty','','inherit','open','closed','','speakers-2016-2','','','2018-07-13 04:39:57','2018-07-13 04:39:57','',191,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/speakers-2016-1.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(193,1,'2018-07-13 04:43:49','2018-07-13 04:43:49','When asked to describe her job, Stacia Martin is likely to smile and reply, “How much time do you have?”\r\n\r\nStacia, who in 2016 celebrates her 38th year with The Walt Disney Company, is based out of Disneyland in California, but spends much of her time on special projects for diverse Disney groups including Walt Disney World, Walt Disney Imagineering, Disney Consumer Products, Walt Disney Records, Disney Destinations, Disney Cruise Line, The Walt Disney Archives, the Disney Legends program, D23, Disney Interactive, Walt Disney Studios Home Entertainment, Disney Entertainment Productions and the ABC Cable Networks Group.\r\n\r\nAn early predilection for art led Stacia to focus her professional goals at age seven during a third grade “career day.” Self-trained “with refinements” (Illustration Studies at California State University), Stacia began her Disney job a week and a day after her high school graduation.\r\n\r\nAt first, it was not strictly art or the tricky “quick sketch” skills that occupied her time; as an avid Disney fan and collector, Stacia first found her niche in the original Disneyana Shop on Main Street in Disneyland. There, and later when opening The Disney Gallery in New Orleans Square, she enjoyed spending time with Park Guests whose specialized questions were well met by her knowledge of Disney lore. Today Stacia continues to share this history as a writer, creating and presenting illustrated lectures, and with appearances in Disney video documentaries.\r\n\r\nAlongside art assignments, Stacia has enjoyed an array of duties: being an “Audio Art Director” for Walt Disney Imagineering’s New Fantasyland attractions at Disneyland, an “Audio Archeologist” for the innovative Disneyland Forever digital system, and spearheading the restoration of one of her favorite films, Walt Disney’s 1967 musical The Happiest Millionaire.\r\n\r\nSince 1985, Stacia has traveled extensively for Disney. In 2001 she opened the preview center for Hong Kong Disneyland, and exotic locales such as Australia, Indonesia, Scotland and Singapore have shared her calendar with trips throughout the USA.\r\n\r\nRecent assignments have continued in their variety: illustrating books, designing collectibles, creating specialty art, and enjoying a multimedia presence across radio, television and podcasts. Favorite writing projects include The Sounds of Disneyland, the elegant book accompanying Walt Disney Records’ 50th Anniversary CD box set A Musical History of Disneyland, and Walt Disney and the 1964 World’s Fair, included in a 5 CD celebration one of the most innovative periods in Disney history. Stacia was also tapped to write the historic liner notes for The Walt Disney Legacy Collection’s 2015 CD release honoring the 60th anniversary of Disneyland.\r\n\r\nStacia says that some of her favorite moments are the simplest ones… particularly the time spent drawing for children. “To watch a child’s face light up when three circles suddenly become Mickey Mouse before their eyes, and then to show them that this is something they can learn to do, too–their reactions, to me, are the true definition of Disney’s magic.”\r\n\r\nShe is particularly proud to have been named to the inaugural “classes” of both Walt Disney Legacy and Disney “Archives Angels” award recipients. “Being able to carry on the legacy of Walt Disney and his original staff…to create images for people that will mean as much to them as their predecessors have to me…it’s not a job, it’s a privilege.”','Stacia Martin','','publish','closed','closed','','stacia-martin','','','2018-07-13 04:44:21','2018-07-13 04:44:21','',0,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/?post_type=guest_speakers&#038;p=193',0,'guest_speakers','',0),(194,1,'2018-07-13 04:43:59','2018-07-13 04:43:59','','stacia','','inherit','open','closed','','speakers-2016-3','','','2018-07-13 04:44:18','2018-07-13 04:44:18','',193,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/speakers-2016-2.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(195,1,'2018-07-13 04:48:44','2018-07-13 04:48:44','Kerry answered an audition call during the planning stages of the animated feature film <i>Peter Pan</i>. The audition, supervised by animator Marc Davis, required her to pantomime the motions that would be used as live-action reference for the animation of Tinker Bell. As Tinker Bell was to be non verbal, her movements would be integral, and Davis sought a dancer that could help embody the character. Kerry won the part and spent six months at the Disney Studios on a mostly empty sound stage pantomiming the part. The studios provided props, notably a giant keyhole mounted on a stand as well as a pair of giant scissors, used in the scene where Tinker Bell became trapped in a jewelry box. Kerry also provided the voice and reference movements of the red-haired mermaid in the Neverland lagoon scene.','Margaret Kerry','','publish','closed','closed','','margaret-kerry','','','2019-01-23 16:20:02','2019-01-23 16:20:02','',0,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/?post_type=guest_speakers&#038;p=195',0,'guest_speakers','',0),(197,1,'2018-07-13 04:49:38','2018-07-13 04:49:38','','Margaret_Kerry_1','','inherit','open','closed','','margaret_kerry_1','','','2018-07-13 04:49:46','2018-07-13 04:49:46','',195,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Margaret_Kerry_1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(198,1,'2018-07-13 04:53:49','2018-07-13 04:53:49','<b>Mark Silverman</b> is an American voice actor who voiced <a title=\"Rod Serling\" href=\"http://disney.wikia.com/wiki/Rod_Serling\">Rod Serling</a> in <i><a title=\"The Twilight Zone Tower of Terror\" href=\"http://disney.wikia.com/wiki/The_Twilight_Zone_Tower_of_Terror\">The Twilight Zone Tower of Terror</a></i> attractions at the <a title=\"Walt Disney Parks and Resorts\" href=\"http://disney.wikia.com/wiki/Walt_Disney_Parks_and_Resorts\">Disney parks</a>. He also voiced <a title=\"Friend Owl\" href=\"http://disney.wikia.com/wiki/Friend_Owl\">Friend Owl</a> in many <i><a title=\"Bambi (film)\" href=\"http://disney.wikia.com/wiki/Bambi_(film)\">Bambi</a></i> projects and provided several voices in the <a title=\"Magic Kingdom\" href=\"http://disney.wikia.com/wiki/Magic_Kingdom\">Magic Kingdom</a> interactive attraction <i><a title=\"A Pirate\'s Adventure: Treasures of the Seven Seas\" href=\"http://disney.wikia.com/wiki/A_Pirate%27s_Adventure:_Treasures_of_the_Seven_Seas\">A Pirate\'s Adventure: Treasures of the Seven Seas</a></i>.\r\n\r\nAside from voicing Friend Owl, Silverman also played the voice of a Grasshopper who never made it past the <i>Bambi</i> storyboards, and is now brought to life in a special deleted scene segment on the new Blu-ray edition of <i>Bambi</i>. He also narrated several bonus features on the <i><a title=\"Zootopia\" href=\"http://disney.wikia.com/wiki/Zootopia\">Zootopia</a></i> Blu-ray.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, Silverman has voiced characters in several Disney dubs of <a title=\"Studio Ghibli\" href=\"http://disney.wikia.com/wiki/Studio_Ghibli\">Studio Ghibli</a> films, including the King in Miyazaki\'s <i><a title=\"Howl\'s Moving Castle\" href=\"http://disney.wikia.com/wiki/Howl%27s_Moving_Castle\">Howl\'s Moving Castle</a></i> and King Jihl in Miyazaki\'s <i><a title=\"Nausicaä of the Valley of the Wind\" href=\"http://disney.wikia.com/wiki/Nausica%C3%A4_of_the_Valley_of_the_Wind\">Nausicaä of the Valley of the Wind</a></i>.\r\n\r\nAnother one of Silverman\'s favorite Disney voice projects was getting to re-voice <a title=\"Fred MacMurray\" href=\"http://disney.wikia.com/wiki/Fred_MacMurray\">Fred MacMurray</a> for the restoration of <i><a title=\"The Happiest Millionaire\" href=\"http://disney.wikia.com/wiki/The_Happiest_Millionaire\">The Happiest Millionaire</a></i>, which was the last live-action film that <a title=\"Walt Disney\" href=\"http://disney.wikia.com/wiki/Walt_Disney\">Walt Disney</a> personally supervised.','Mark Silverman','','publish','closed','closed','','mark-silverman','','','2018-07-13 04:53:49','2018-07-13 04:53:49','',0,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/?post_type=guest_speakers&#038;p=198',0,'guest_speakers','',0),(199,1,'2018-07-13 04:53:40','2018-07-13 04:53:40','','580-MarkSilverman','','inherit','open','closed','','580-marksilverman','','','2018-07-13 04:53:46','2018-07-13 04:53:46','',198,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/580-MarkSilverman.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(200,1,'2018-07-13 05:00:03','2018-07-13 05:00:03','','2016','','inherit','open','closed','','2016-2','','','2018-07-13 05:00:09','2018-07-13 05:00:09','',187,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/2016.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(201,1,'2018-07-13 05:07:46','2018-07-13 05:07:46','','PNW Mouse Meets','','inherit','closed','closed','','31-revision-v1','','','2018-07-13 05:07:46','2018-07-13 05:07:46','',31,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/31-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(202,1,'2018-07-13 05:09:03','2018-07-13 05:09:03','','PNW Mouse Meets','','inherit','closed','closed','','31-revision-v1','','','2018-07-13 05:09:03','2018-07-13 05:09:03','',31,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/31-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(203,1,'2018-07-13 05:12:24','2018-07-13 05:12:24','','2017 PNW Mouse Meet','','publish','closed','closed','','2017-pnw-mouse-meet','','','2018-07-13 05:12:24','2018-07-13 05:12:24','',0,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/?post_type=envira&#038;p=203',0,'envira','',0),(204,1,'2018-07-13 05:11