'','inherit','closed','closed','','31-revision-v1','','','2019-02-20 04:47:27','2019-02-20 04:47:27','',31,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/31-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(653,1,'2019-02-20 04:50:21','2019-02-20 04:50:21','<div id=\"wsb-canvas-template-container\">\n<div id=\"wsb-element-1bf5ac62-004b-48a6-818b-0dab5d2a1d63\" class=\"wsb-element-text\" data-type=\"element\">\n<div class=\"txt \">\n\n<span class=\"editor_footer\">Copyright Pacific Northwest Mouse Meet™ LLC. All rights reserved.</span><span class=\"editor_footer\">​\nThis website is not part of, endorsed or authorized by, or affiliated with the Walt Disney Company or it\'s affiliates.\nVisit the official Disney website at Disney.com </span>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"wsb-element-e7d3f901-259a-475a-93c3-75f26a1fcb44\" class=\"wsb-element-text\" data-type=\"element\">\n<div class=\"txt \">\n\n<strong>When is the PNW Mouse Meet?</strong>\nThe PNW Mouse Meet is set for Saturday July 14th from 10:00am to 6:30pm (Times subject to change). This is a one day event. Please check the EVENTS Details Page to see more details about the day of event as they become available.\n\n<strong>Is this event part of the Disney Company?</strong>\nNo. This event is in no way affiliated with the Walt Disney Company and/or any of its affiliates. This event has been created by Disney Fans for Disney Fans and is considered an Unofficial Disney Fan Event.\n\n<strong>How can I get tickets for the event?</strong>\nTickets are for sale ONLY on our website. Visit the Event Page for details. Tickets are limited to ensure an intimate experience and Tickets have Sold Out every year. No tickets will be available at the venue.\n\n<strong>Can I get tickets at the door?</strong>\nNO tickets will be available the day of the event or at the door.\n\n<strong>Are there hotels nearby I can stay at?</strong>\nYes. The Embassy Suites Hotel in Lynnwood is once again our official hotel partner. Check out the Official Hotel Link on the PNWMM Event Page. There are also a variety of other Hotel options nearby, just click on the CONVENTION CENTER Info Box on the PNWMM Main Page to learn more.\n\n<strong>Can I bring my camera or video camera?</strong>\nYes. There will be many photo opportunities with Celebrities, Authors, Podcasters, Displays, other Disney Fans and surprises. Photos and video are allowed in all areas of the events space. <strong>There is NO Audio or Video recording allowed </strong>during Guest Speaker Presentations. Photographs are ok.\n\n<strong>Will it cost for Guest Celebrity Autographs:</strong>\nOur Celebrity Guest Speakers will be available for Meet &amp; Greet opportunities. Each Celebrity may have items for sale and/or may charge for autographs. This is up to the individual and is at their own discretion. Ask a PNWMM Team Member for details at the Meet/Greet areas during the event.\n\n<strong>Will there be food available at the event?</strong>\nYes. There will be food items such as pastries, sandwiches, salads, beverages, snacks, treats and more available for purchase at the convention center Café for your convenience. There are also several restaurants nearby and within walking distance.\n\n<strong>Can I bring Disney Items to sell at the PNW Mouse Meet?</strong>\nYou must be a Registered Vendor in order to sell items at the PNW Mouse Meet event. No other unauthorized selling of items is allowed at the event and may be grounds for removal from the event without ticket refund or compensation. For future Vendor consideration, please email us at vendorinfo@pnwmousemeet.com for more information on how to become a vendor at this event.\n\n<strong>Can I bring or hand out Business Cards, Information or Advertising at the event?</strong>\n\nONLY Registered &amp; Paid Vendors are allowed to solicit and sell things to our Guests. No other solicitations of any kind are allowed. Any Guests violating this rule may be asked to leave the event. For future Vendor consideration, please email us at vendorinfo@pnwmousemeet.com for more information on how to become a vendor at this event.\n\n<strong>Is there an ATM at the Convention Center?</strong>\nThere is <strong>NO ATM </strong>at the Convention Center. There are several Banks with ATMs within 4 blocks of the Convention Center.\n\n<strong>Does PNWMM and/or Vendors accept Credit Card at the event?</strong>\nThe PNWMM Booth does accept cash and credit cards. Each Vendor is an individual entity and may or may not accept credit cards however many do. <strong>The Charity Raffle Tickets are Cash Only.</strong> Celebrity fees for autographs or other items for sale may be cash only.\n\n<strong>Can I Dress Up in Costume for the PNW Mouse Meet?</strong>\n\nWe welcome Guests who  are Disney Bounding or Cosplay. We do not allow weapons such as knives, swords or other dangerous items. We also do not allow items that LOOK like dangerous weapons. Things like Light Sabers or Thor\'s Hammer is acceptable. We look forward to seeing many amazing Cosplay and Bounding this year!\n\n<strong>Can I or my company be a Sponsor of the PNW Mouse Meet?</strong>\nWe are accepting inquiries and applications for quality businesses that fit our Partner Profile as a Sponsor of future PNW Mouse Meet events. Please email us at sponsorinfo@pnwmousemeet.com or contact us for more information.\n\nIf you have a specific question you would like answered regarding the PNW Mouse Meet, please visit the CONTACT US tab at the top of the page to submit your question.\n\nThank you!\nPNW Mouse Meet Team.\n\n\n\n<em><strong>The PNW Mouse Meet™ is an Unofficial Disney Fan Event. The PNW Mouse Meet™ is not affiliated with the Walt Disney Company or any of its affiliates or subsidiaries. Visit the Official Disney website at www.disney.com</strong></em>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>','Frequently Asked Questions','','inherit','closed','closed','','174-autosave-v1','','','2019-02-20 04:50:21','2019-02-20 04:50:21','',174,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/174-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(654,1,'2022-03-02 02:19:13','2022-03-02 02:19:13','<h2>Door Decorating Information</h2>\nBy choosing to book a PNW Mouse Meet Group Rate Room at the Embassy Suites in Lynnwood during the weekend of the PNWMM, you can take advantage of ALL the Group Benefits as well as participate in the VERY Popular Room Door &amp; Window Decorating Contest!!\n\nGuest Room Door &amp; Window Decorating Contest!\n\n<h2>Prizes</h2>\nWe will be awarding prizes for the THREE (3) Best Disney Themed Hotel Room Windows. Ro\n<ol>\n 	<li>Most Creative</li>\n 	<li>Best Theming</li>\n 	<li>Best In Show</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>Important Information</h2>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Decoration Judging will take place between 9:30pm &amp; 10pm by PNWMM Cast Members.</li>\n 	<li>You are welcome to begin decorating as soon as you check in Friday afternoon!</li>\n 	<li><strong>Room Window dimensions: 43½ inches Wide X 76½ inches Tall</strong></li>\n 	<li>Room Door is normal size Door.</li>\n</ul>\n<u><strong>NOTE:</strong></u><strong>\nThe Windows to each room are now FROSTED and you are Unable to see through the Windows! We highly recommend decorating the OUTSIDE of the Window and Door ONLY.</strong>\n\n[smartslider3 slider=7]\n\n<em><strong>The Hotel has also asked that we pass along the following rules for the decoration contest:</strong></em>\n\nDecoration should NOT block public walkways, hallways, door entries or railings\nGuest occupying room is responsible for all cleanup and disposal of decorations\nItems APPROVED to use: Blue Painter’s Tape, Post It Note type sticky back paper, suction cups and other items that will NOT leave a residue or any other markings.\nNO nails, thumbtacks, glue, super glue, duct tape or any other item that would leave a mark, hole, scratches, sticky residue or other defects on doors, windows, walls, etc.\nEmbassy Suites will hold the Room Guest fully responsible and liable for any damage that may occur.\n\nWe ask that you be respectful of other guests and the hotel’s rules.\nHave a GREAT time decorating and we are SO excited to see what you come up with!!\n\nIf you should have any questions please contact us a hotel@pnwmousemeet.com','Room Window Decorating Contest','','inherit','closed','closed','','176-autosave-v1','','','2022-03-02 02:19:13','2022-03-02 02:19:13','',176,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/176-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(655,1,'2022-03-23 21:20:18','2022-03-23 21:20:18','<h2>Join Us at the Embassy Suites!</h2>\n<p class=\"intro\">The 2022 PNW Mouse Meet room block is now available!</p>\nPNW Mouse Meet Group Rate bookings are now available for King Suite room types. Be sure to secure your rooms as soon as possible to ensure you get the room type you want.\n\nWe can’t wait to see you there and get the weekend festivities started!!\n\n<strong>PNW Mouse Meet 2022 special rate</strong>\n$215 King Suite.\n\n<a class=\"btn btn-primary\" href=\"\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Book Online!</a>\n\nGuests can also call in their reservations at <a href=\"tel:4257752500\">(425) 775-2500</a> and reserving their rooms under the <strong>PNW Mouse Meet 2022</strong>.\n\n<hr />\n\n<h3>Details</h3>\n<strong>The Pacific Northwest Mouse Meet 2022 Special Rate will INCLUDE:</strong>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Daily hot buffet breakfast buffet that includes hot and cold options: Monday -Friday 6am -9am; Saturday &amp; Sunday 7am-10:30am</li>\n 	<li>Nightly evening reception available from 5:00pm – 6:30pm that include (2) complimentary beer, wine, cocktails, and light appetizers</li>\n 	<li>Newly renovated large two room suites</li>\n 	<li>On-site restaurant &amp; bar serving dinner Sunday through Thursday 5:00pm-9:00pm, Friday &amp; Saturday 5:00pm-10:00pm</li>\n 	<li>Indoor pool and whirlpool open 7am to 10pm, adult only 10pm-11pm</li>\n 	<li>Precor fitness facility open 24 hours</li>\n 	<li>Free parking</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Hotel Events</h3>\nCome join us for all the fun!\n\n<a class=\"btn btn-primary\" href=\"/friday-night-events/\">Friday Night Events</a>\n\n<a class=\"btn btn-secondary\" href=\"/mouse_meet_info_item/room-window-decorating-contest/\">Window Decorating Rules</a>\n<h3>About the Hotel</h3>\nThere are now so many of our Event Guests that stay at this Hotel that over the years we have built up the Friday evening events to be a fantastic way to kick off the PNWMM Weekend, meet other Guests and have a whole lot of fun!\n\n​From Interactive Games, Room Window Decorating Contests, Interactive Trivia Games and other added benefits... Embassy Suites is THE place to stay with free parking and is located less than 1 mile from the Lynnwood Convention Center!\n\n​NOTE: The Embassy Suites recently renovated the entire hotel with all new refreshed rooms,\n\natrium, seating area, restaurant, meetings space and more.\n\n​We have negotiated fantastic Group Room Rates that include the following for Guests booking at this hotel:​\n\nFree Wi-Fi; Children under 18 no additional cost; Free Hot Breakfast each morning of your stay; Every room is a Suite; Free Admission to the PNWMM Friday Night Events including games, activities, Trivia Contest, music and more; and ability to participate in the very popular Hotel Room Window Decorating Contest.','PNWMM Partner Hotel | Embassy Suites Lynnwood','','inherit','closed','closed','','220-autosave-v1','','','2022-03-23 21:20:18','2022-03-23 21:20:18','',220,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/220-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(656,1,'2019-02-24 20:20:16','2019-02-24 20:20:16','<div id=\"wsb-element-3bb85533-e9db-4d83-9dc8-47bff2cd65d0\" class=\"wsb-element-text\" data-type=\"element\">\r\n<div class=\"txt \"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"wsb-element-399ae084-d95e-4a76-9412-0b5ec4b163fd\" class=\"wsb-element-text\" data-type=\"element\">\r\n<div class=\"txt \">\r\n<h2>About the Events</h2>\r\nThe PNW Mouse Meet is an unofficial Disney Fan Event that was created by Disney Fans FOR Disney Fans. This annual event provides Disney enthusiasts the opportunity to get together right here in the Pacific Northwest to share and celebrate all things Disney.\r\n\r\nThe PNW Mouse Meet is comprised of a variety of experiences including:\r\nDisney Celebrities, Disney podcasters, authors, and travel experts, Disneyana Collectibles Vendors, Disney Fan Collection Displays, Pin Trading, Trivia, Food, magical surprises, fantastic auction items with proceeds going to charity, Disney Fans meeting fellow Disney Fans, A little magic, a little pixie dust and so much more.\r\n\r\nThe inaugural PNW Mouse Meet event took place on Saturday August 15, 2009 at the Lynnwood Convention Center and has grown from 150 Guests to over 400 Guests today.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2>Our PNW Mouse Meet Team:</h2>\r\n<div class=\"flex-container\">\r\n<div class=\"col\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-428\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px;\" src=\"https://pnwmousemeet.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/cf0bfea9f2c56fbbe32846cf6e6dd886.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"223\" height=\"242\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"col\" style=\"flex-grow: 2;\">\r\n<h3>Don Morin</h3>\r\n<h4>Founder/Host</h4>\r\nSince 2009 Don and his team have been creating a magical experience for thousands of Guests.\r\n\"Passion, Disney Fandom and giving them more than they expect are key ingredients to our success!\"\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"flex-container\">\r\n<div class=\"col\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-429\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px;\" src=\"https://pnwmousemeet.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/1eb0bf4be885c7332a88b09abc007fb8.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"214\" height=\"186\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"col\" style=\"flex-grow: 2;\">\r\n<h3>PNW Mouse Meet Volunteer Team</h3>\r\n<h4>An amazing group of individuals who LOVE making Magic for our Guests.</h4>\r\nMichelle, Marc, Beci, Jonathan, Kurt, John, Jon, Lynn, Anna, Sue, Jenna, Matt, Stephanie, Scott, Erik, Jerry, Marguerite, Matt, Kayla, Shawn and many more...\r\n\r\nWe appreciate all of their time, efforts and excitement!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','About Us','','inherit','closed','closed','','161-revision-v1','','','2019-02-24 20:20:16','2019-02-24 20:20:16','',161,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/161-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(657,1,'2019-02-24 20:23:41','2019-02-24 20:23:41','<div id=\"wsb-element-3bb85533-e9db-4d83-9dc8-47bff2cd65d0\" class=\"wsb-element-text\" data-type=\"element\">\r\n<div class=\"txt \"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"wsb-element-399ae084-d95e-4a76-9412-0b5ec4b163fd\" class=\"wsb-element-text\" data-type=\"element\">\r\n<div class=\"txt \">\r\n<h2>About the Events</h2>\r\nThe PNW Mouse Meet is an unofficial Disney Fan Event that was created by Disney Fans FOR Disney Fans. This annual event provides Disney enthusiasts the opportunity to get together right here in the Pacific Northwest to share and celebrate all things Disney.\r\n\r\nThe PNW Mouse Meet is comprised of a variety of experiences including:\r\nDisney Celebrities, Disney podcasters, authors, and travel experts, Disneyana Collectibles Vendors, Disney Fan Collection Displays, Pin Trading, Trivia, Food, magical surprises, fantastic auction items with proceeds going to charity, Disney Fans meeting fellow Disney Fans, A little magic, a little pixie dust and so much more.\r\n\r\nThe inaugural PNW Mouse Meet event took place on Saturday August 15, 2009 at the Lynnwood Convention Center and has grown from 150 Guests to over 400 Guests today.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2>Our PNW Mouse Meet Team:</h2>\r\n<div class=\"flex-container\">\r\n<div class=\"col\" style=\"flex-grow: 2\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-428\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px;\" src=\"https://pnwmousemeet.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/cf0bfea9f2c56fbbe32846cf6e6dd886.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"223\" height=\"242\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"col\" style=\"flex-grow: 2;\">\r\n<h3>Don Morin</h3>\r\n<h4>Founder/Host</h4>\r\nSince 2009 Don and his team have been creating a magical experience for thousands of Guests.\r\n\"Passion, Disney Fandom and giving them more than they expect are key ingredients to our success!\"\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"flex-container\">\r\n<div class=\"col\" style=\"flex-grow: 2\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-429\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px;\" src=\"https://pnwmousemeet.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/1eb0bf4be885c7332a88b09abc007fb8.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"214\" height=\"186\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"col\" style=\"flex-grow: 2;\">\r\n<h3>PNW Mouse Meet Volunteer Team</h3>\r\n<h4>An amazing group of individuals who LOVE making Magic for our Guests.</h4>\r\nMichelle, Marc, Beci, Jonathan, Kurt, John, Jon, Lynn, Anna, Sue, Jenna, Matt, Stephanie, Scott, Erik, Jerry, Marguerite, Matt, Kayla, Shawn and many more...\r\n\r\nWe appreciate all of their time, efforts and excitement!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','About Us','','inherit','closed','closed','','161-revision-v1','','','2019-02-24 20:23:41','2019-02-24 20:23:41','',161,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/161-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(658,1,'2019-02-24 20:29:30','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Things to Do','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2019-02-24 20:29:30','2019-02-24 20:29:30','',0,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/?post_type=mouse_meet_info_item&#038;p=658',0,'mouse_meet_info_item','',0),(659,1,'2019-02-24 20:32:08','2019-02-24 20:32:08','<h3>When to Arrive and Timing of Events</h3>\r\nCheck in begins at 9am. Rope Drop takes place at 10am and our first Guest Speaker begins at 11:30am. Be sure to arrive early and don’t miss a thing!\r\nDO bring your ID as this is how we will check you in. Bring a smile, camera and a pocket full of Pixie Dust… We will do the rest!\r\n<h3>Food, Snacks, and More!</h3>\r\nThe Lynnwood Convention Center will have three food locations serving sandwiches, salads, pizza, ice cream, popcorn, Mickey Rice Krispy Treats, coffee, sodas and other Disney themed items…. They will even have Mint Juleps with or without a splash of Bourbon! Vegetarian Food options will be available.\r\n<h3>PNWMM Info Booth</h3>\r\nHere you can ask any questions about the event as well as purchase exclusive Limited Edition PNWMM Pins (new design this year!!), a new PNWMM Print, logo shirts, mugs, pens and more!\r\n<a name=\"guest\"></a><a name=\"celebrity\"></a>\r\n<h3>Celebrity Meet &amp; Greets</h3>\r\nAll of our Guest Speakers will be available at various times to meet YOU! Because of high Guest demand to meet Guest Speakers we do have to limit time and items to be signed so that as many Guests can meet them as possible. There may be a charge to meet the Guest Speakers or for Autographs. More details will be confirmed as we get closer to the event date. We ask for your understanding and cooperation so that as many Guests as possible can meet our Guest Speakers. Thank you.\r\n\r\nMore information on Celebrity Meet &amp; Greets will be shared as we get closer to the event.\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Due to ever-changing Convention Center, Government and CDC Covid Protocols, we will update information and rules surrounding meet &amp; greets regularly as things change and/or are updated.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Please continue to check back for the latest information.</p>\r\n<a name=\"photo\"></a>\r\n<h3>PNW Mouse Meet Photo Stops</h3>\r\nBe sure to keep an eye out for PNW Mouse Meet Photo Stops all around the Event space! From amazing one of a kind displays and homages to Disney Park Icons to Disney Park Attractions Vehicles, there will be many unique ways to take that special photo!\r\n<h3>  Fan Displays and PNWMM Photo Opps</h3>\r\nWe will have several amazing Fan created displays for your enjoyment! We have once again worked very hard to Plus Up several displays and to create new and exciting photo opportunities to make magical memories.\r\n\r\n<a name=\"raffle\"></a>\r\n<h3>Raffle for Charity</h3>\r\nWe again this year have put together a number of AMAZING Prize baskets… themed to Mickey Mouse, Walt Disney Imagineering, Club 33, Signed book collections, a Dooney &amp; Bourke bag, luggage and so many other great things. Again this year we will be supporting the Ryman Arts which was founded by Disney Legend Marty Sklar in honor of Disney Legend Herb Ryman, helping underprivileged kids expand on their art skills, stay in school and go on to college and careers. The other benefactor of our Charity dollars is Seattle Children\'s Hospital. We are proud to support both\r\nof these fine charities. The Raffle Tickets are Cash Only so please be sure to bring enough to support your needs for Tickets. There is NO ATM on premise and there nearest bank is a couple of blocks away. You are going to LOVE these charity raffle prizes!!\r\n<a name=\"disneyana\"></a>\r\n<h3>Disneyana Vendors</h3>\r\nWe are excited for the variety of Vendors this year… some new and some past favorites! Authors, Art, Jewelry, Custom Ears, Ornaments and so much more! Some Vendors only accept cash and others accept credit cards. Be sure to be prepared for both. You can visit our website to see a full list of Vendors at the 2022 PNWMM <a href=\"https://pnwmousemeet.com/pnw_mouse_meets/2020/\">here.</a>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"cosplay\"></a>\r\n<h3>Disney-Bounding &amp; Cosplay</h3>\r\nWe LOVE seeing all the amazing costumes, bounding, ears, shoes, hats and so many other creative wearables…\r\n\r\nJust a few rules: Please ensure your costumes and bounding are themed to Disney, safe, no weapons and is in good taste. PNWMM Team has the right to ask that dangerous items or inappropriate costumes be left in vehicles or at home. Guests that don’t follow these and other\r\nrules may be asked to leave.\r\n\r\nYou may be photographed, or video recorded by PNWMM, Media or other Guests. We appreciate the work you put into your outfits and we can’t wait to see what you have created!!\r\n\r\n<a name=\"fans\"></a>\r\n<h3>Opportunity to Meet Other Disney Fans</h3>\r\nOne thing we’ve learned over the past 12 years, is that there have been SO many connections and friendships made at all the PNW Mouse Meet events through the years...One couple even met and got married! So don’t be shy about saying hello to every other Disney Fan you come across at the event...Remember...We ALL have the same thing in common!! So look forward to seeing old friends and meeting new ones as well! And be sure to say hello to our PNWMM Team in the PNWMM Team Shirts!...They work hard so that you can have a Magical Day! And come say hello to me (Don) too! We would love to chat with you!\r\n\r\nWe can\'t wait to meet YOU!\r\n\r\nIf you have other questions please email us at <a href=\"mailto:info@pnwmousemeet.com\">info@pnwmousemeet.com</a>','Know Before You Go','','publish','closed','closed','','things-to-do-at-the-mouse-meet','','','2022-01-27 21:58:12','2022-01-27 21:58:12','',0,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/?page_id=659',0,'page','',0),(660,1,'2019-02-24 20:32:08','2019-02-24 20:32:08','GUEST CELEBRITY STAGE PRESENTATIONS:\r\nEach year we host several Disney related Guest Speakers. In the past we have had Imagineers, Animators, Voice Actors, A Disneyland President, Movie Producers and Disney Legends including Marty Sklar, Bob Gurr, Don Hahn, Kevin Rafferty, Glenn Barker, Margaret Kerry, Bill Farmer, Tony Baxter, Stacia Martin, Mike Peraza and many more...\r\nWho will it be in 2018? Check back here for details after announcements are made. We can\'t wait!\r\n\r\nCELEBRITY MEET &amp; GREETS:\r\nWe are extremely excited to have the opportunity to host a number of Disney Celebrities during the day. Autographs will be available and varies by celebrity guest. Autograph Rules: Limit of 1 item to autograph plus the PNWMM collectible Autograph Card provided in Guest Gift Bags and 1 photograph. This rule is in place so that we are able to provide everyone an opportunity to meet the celebrities. Please be considerate of others by adhering to these simple rules.  PNW MOUSE MEET PHOTO STOPS: Be sure to keep an eye out for PNW Mouse Meet Photo Stops all around the Event space! From amazing one of a kind displays and homages to Disney Park Icons to Disney Park Attractions Vehicles, there will be many unique ways to take that special photo!  FAN\r\n\r\nDISPLAYS AND PHOTO OPPS:\r\nWe will have several amazing Fan created displays for your enjoyment! We have once again worked very hard to Plus Up several displays and to create new and exciting photo opportunities to make magical memories.\r\n\r\nRAFFLE FOR CHARITY:\r\nThe PNW Mouse Meet Team and founder Don Morin are extremely dedicated to charitable causes. The team has been working hard to secure AMAZING Disney Collectibles and Experiences that will be available for Raffle and Auction at this year’s event. We will once again be supporting the Ryman Arts Foundation which was started by Disney Legend Marty Sklar to help high school students further their arts education. We will ALSO be supporting the Seattle Children’s Hospital. As we get together to celebrate all things Disney at this year’s PNW Mouse Meet, we hope that you will join us in supporting these very worthy causes and enjoy the opportunity to win some amazing prizes as well!\r\n\r\nDISNEYANA VENDORS:\r\nEach year we have a number of AMAZING Disneyana sellers that come from all over the Pacific Northwest and from as far away as California! Check back here as we will be posting a listing of Disneyana Sellers soon.\r\n\r\nDISNEY-BOUNDING &amp; COSPLAY: We love to see our attendees dress up in all sorts of creative and interesting costumes! Disney-Bounding and  Cosplay have become ever popular. In celebration, we will be hosting a special Cosplay &amp; Bounding Parade across the PNWMM Stage during the day of the event!\r\nFor the sake of safety, we do have some rules about what costumes and props are acceptable at PNW Mouse Meet™ events. When planning your costume, please keep the following rules in mind: Disney related Properties Disney-Bounding and Cosplay only. Disney, Pixar, Star Wars, Marvel, Disney Parks, etc. Decency and Appropriateness: Attire, costumes and props must be PG-rated. Improper language is not permitted on attire or props of any kind. Costume Safety: Costumes must not be dangerous to anyone who bumps into them accidentally.  Costumes and props that pose an indoor safety hazard to their owners, such as stilts, roller blades, etc, are also not allowed. Weapons: No weapons of any kind are permitted. Any prop being used in an unsafe or threatening manner may be confiscated by Security. Security may ask you at any time to put a prop away or change out of a costume based on its acceptability. The Manager on Duty of Security has the final say as to the acceptability of any prop or costume.\r\n\r\nOPPORTUNITY TO MEET OTHER DISNEY FANS:\r\nWith all the wonderful speakers, amazing activities, games, celebrities, food, and Disneyana, let’s not lose sight of one thing...Disney Fans! Some of the greatest memories that came out of previous year’s events were the opportunities for Disney Fans to meet other Disney Fans. At work, at school, and within our own families, it is often difficult to convey the Passion for Disney that we all share. Here you can meet hundreds of Disney Fans who are just like YOU. Many friendships, relationships and even marriages (yes a marriage) have happened by meeting people at the PNWMM!\r\n\r\nWe can\'t wait to meet YOU!','Things to Do At the Mouse Meet','','inherit','closed','closed','','659-revision-v1','','','2019-02-24 20:32:08','2019-02-24 20:32:08','',659,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/659-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(661,1,'2019-02-24 20:38:06','2019-02-24 20:38:06','','walt disney','','inherit','open','closed','','walt-disney','','','2019-02-24 20:38:06','2019-02-24 20:38:06','',0,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/walt-disney.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(662,1,'2019-02-24 20:38:07','2019-02-24 20:38:07','','kinsfather15','','inherit','open','closed','','kinsfather15','','','2019-02-24 20:38:07','2019-02-24 20:38:07','',0,'https://pnwmousemeet