sb-element-text\" data-type=\"element\">\r\n<div class=\"txt \">\r\n<h2>About the Events</h2>\r\nThe PNW Mouse Meet is an unofficial Disney Fan Event that was created by Disney Fans FOR Disney Fans. This annual event provides Disney enthusiasts the opportunity to get together right here in the Pacific Northwest to share and celebrate all things Disney.\r\n\r\nThe PNW Mouse Meet is comprised of a variety of experiences including:\r\nDisney Celebrities, Disney podcasters, authors, and travel experts, Disneyana Collectibles Vendors, Disney Fan Collection Displays, Pin Trading, Trivia, Food, magical surprises, fantastic auction items with proceeds going to charity, Disney Fans meeting fellow Disney Fans, A little magic, a little pixie dust and so much more.\r\n\r\nThe inaugural PNW Mouse Meet event took place on Saturday August 15, 2009 at the Lynnwood Convention Center and has grown from 150 Guests to over 400 Guests today.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2>Our PNW Mouse Meet Team:</h2>\r\n<div class=\"flex-container\">\r\n<div class=\"col\" style=\"flex-grow: 2;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-428\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px;\" src=\"https://pnwmousemeet.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/cf0bfea9f2c56fbbe32846cf6e6dd886.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"223\" height=\"242\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"col\" style=\"flex-grow: 2;\">\r\n<h3>Don Morin</h3>\r\n<h4>Founder/Host</h4>\r\nSince 2009 Don and his team have been creating a magical experience for thousands of Guests.\r\n\"Passion, Disney Fandom and giving them more than they expect are key ingredients to our success!\"\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"flex-container\">\r\n<div class=\"col\" style=\"flex-grow: 2;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-429\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px;\" src=\"https://pnwmousemeet.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/1eb0bf4be885c7332a88b09abc007fb8.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"214\" height=\"186\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"col\" style=\"flex-grow: 2;\">\r\n<h3>PNW Mouse Meet Volunteer Team</h3>\r\n<h4>An amazing group of individuals who LOVE making Magic for our Guests.</h4>\r\nMichelle, Marc, Beci, Jonathan, Kurt, John, Jon, Lynn, Anna, Sue, Jenna, Matt, Stephanie, Scott, Erik, Jerry, Marguerite, Matt, Kayla, Shawn and many more...\r\n\r\nWe appreciate all of their time, efforts and excitement!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','About Us','','inherit','closed','closed','','161-revision-v1','','','2019-02-28 01:01:19','2019-02-28 01:01:19','',161,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/161-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(678,1,'2019-02-28 01:01:41','2019-02-28 01:01:41','<div id=\"wsb-element-3bb85533-e9db-4d83-9dc8-47bff2cd65d0\" class=\"wsb-element-text\" data-type=\"element\">\r\n<div class=\"txt \"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"wsb-element-399ae084-d95e-4a76-9412-0b5ec4b163fd\" class=\"wsb-element-text\" data-type=\"element\">\r\n<div class=\"txt \">\r\n<h2>About the Events</h2>\r\nThe PNW Mouse Meet is an unofficial Disney Fan Event that was created by Disney Fans FOR Disney Fans. This annual event provides Disney enthusiasts the opportunity to get together right here in the Pacific Northwest to share and celebrate all things Disney.\r\n\r\nThe PNW Mouse Meet is comprised of a variety of experiences including:\r\nDisney Celebrities, Disney podcasters, authors, and travel experts, Disneyana Collectibles Vendors, Disney Fan Collection Displays, Pin Trading, Trivia, Food, magical surprises, fantastic auction items with proceeds going to charity, Disney Fans meeting fellow Disney Fans, A little magic, a little pixie dust and so much more.\r\n\r\nThe inaugural PNW Mouse Meet event took place on Saturday August 15, 2009 at the Lynnwood Convention Center and has grown from 150 Guests to over 400 Guests today.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2>Our PNW Mouse Meet Team:</h2>\r\n<div class=\"flex-container\">\r\n<div class=\"col\" style=\"flex-grow: 2;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-428\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px;\" src=\"https://pnwmousemeet.com/wp-content/u