iv>','2019 Vendors','','inherit','closed','closed','','751-revision-v1','','','2019-07-23 14:58:37','2019-07-23 14:58:37','',751,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/751-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(873,1,'2019-07-23 15:07:15','2019-07-23 15:07:15','<h3>When to Arrive and Timing of Events</h3>\r\nCheck in begins at 9am. Rope Drop takes place at 10am and our first Guest Speaker begins at 11am. Be sure to arrive early and don’t miss a thing!\r\nDO bring your ID as this is how we will check you in. Bring a smile, camera and a pocket full of Pixie Dust… We will do the rest!\r\n\r\n<h3>Food, Snacks, and More!</h3>\r\nThe Lynnwood Convention Center will have three food locations serving Sandwiches, Salads, Pizza, Ice Cream, Popcorn, Mickey Rice Krispy Treats, Coffee, Sodas and so much more. They will even have Mint Juleps with or without a splash of Bourbon! Vegetarian Food options will be available.\r\n\r\n<h3>PNWMM Info Booth</h3>\r\nHere you can ask any questions about the event as well as purchase books pertaining to our Author Jeff Kurtti, purchase exclusive Limited Edition PNWMM Pins (new design this year!!), a new PNWMM Print featuring and celebrating the Haunted Mansion’s 50 th , logo mugs, pens and more!\r\n\r\n<a name=\"guest\"></a>\r\n<h3>Guest Celebrity Stage Presentations</h3>\r\nEach year we host several Disney related Guest Speakers. In the past we have had Imagineers, Animators, Voice Actors, A Disneyland President, Movie Producers and Disney Legends including Marty Sklar, Bob Gurr, Don Hahn, Kevin Rafferty, Glenn Barker, Margaret Kerry, Bill Farmer, Tony Baxter, Stacia Martin, Mike Peraza, Charity Carter, Kevin Kidney &amp; Jody Daily, Bill Rogers &amp; Camille Dixon, and many more...\r\nWho will it be in 2019? Check back here for details after announcements are made. We can\'t wait!\r\n<a name=\"celebrity\"></a>\r\n<h3>Celebrity Meet & Greets</h3>\r\nAll of our Guest Speakers, Jeff Kurtti, Ron Clements and Joe Rohde will be available at various times to meet YOU! Because of high Guest demand to meet Guest Speakers we do have to limit time and items to be signed so that as many Guests can meet them as possible.\r\nThere will be no charge to meet the Guest Speakers or for Autographs. \r\n<p>\r\n<strong>For Joe & Ron</strong>, there is a limit of <strong>ONE item</strong> to bring and have signed per person. In addition, you\r\ncan also have your 2019 PNWMM Autograph Card and/or PNWMM Guide Map signed by them as well. You can pick these up at check in for the event.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nFor <strong>Jeff Kurtti</strong>, he has authored so many amazing books… You are welcome to bring up to <strong>2 books</strong> per person to have signed and in addition, the PNWMM Autograph Card and/or Guide Map. We ask for your understanding and cooperation so that as many Guests as possible can meet our\r\nGuest Speakers. Thank you.\r\n</p>\r\n<a name=\"photo\"></a>\r\n<h3>PNW Mouse Meet Photo Stops</h3>\r\nBe sure to keep an eye out for PNW Mouse Meet Photo Stops all around the Event space! From amazing one of a kind displays and homages to Disney Park Icons to Disney Park Attractions Vehicles, there will be many unique ways to take that special photo!\r\n<h3>  Fan Displays and Photo Opps</h3>\r\nWe will have several amazing Fan created displays for your enjoyment! We have once again worked very hard to Plus Up several displays and to create new and exciting photo opportunities to make magical memories.\r\n<a name=\"raffle\"></a>\r\n<h3>Raffle for Charity</h3>\r\nWe again this year have put together a number of AMAZING Prize baskets… themed to Mickey Mouse, Walt Disney Imagineering, Club 33, Signed book collections, a Dooney &amp; Bourke bag, luggage and so many other great things. Again this year we will be supporting the Ryman Arts which was founded by Disney Legend Marty Sklar in honor of Disney Legend Herb Ryman, helping underprivileged kids expand on their art skills, stay in school and go on to college and careers. The other benefactor of our Charity dollars is Seattle Childrens Hospital. We are proud to support both\r\nof these fine charities. The Raffle Tickets are Cash Only so please be sure to bring enough to support your needs for Tickets. There is NO ATM on premise and there nearest bank is a couple of blocks away. You are going to LOVE these charity raffle prizes!!\r\n<a name=\"disneyana\"></a>\r\n<h3>Disneyana Vendors</h3>\r\nWe are excited for the variety of Vendors this year… some new and some past favorites! Authors, Art, Jewelry, Custom Ears, Ornaments and so much more! Some Vendors only accept cash and others accept credit cards. Be sure to be prepared for both. You can visit our website to see a full list of Vendors at the 2019 PNWMM <a href=\"https://pnwmousemeet.com/pnw_mouse_meets/2019/\">here.</a>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"cosplay\"></a>\r\n<h3>Disney-Bounding & Cosplay</h3>\r\nWe LOVE seeing all the amazing costumes, bounding, ears, shoes, hats and so many other creative wearables…\r\n<p>Just a few rules: Please ensure your costumes and bounding are themed to Disney, safe, no weapons and is in good taste. PNWMM Team has the right to ask that dangerous items or inappropriate costumes be left in vehicles or at home. Guests that don’t follow these and other\r\nrules may be asked to leave.</p>\r\n<p>You may be photographed, or video recorded by PNWMM, Media or other Guests. We appreciate the work you put into your outfits and we can’t wait to see what you have created!!</p>\r\n<a name=\"fans\"></a>\r\n<h3>Opportunity to Meet Other Disney Fans</h3>\r\nOne thing we’ve learned over the past 11 years, is that there have been SO many connections and friendships made at all the PNW Mouse Meet events through the years...One couple even met and got married! So don’t be shy about saying hello to every other Disney Fan you come across at the event...Remember...We ALL have the same thing in common!! So look forward to seeing old friends and meeting new ones as well! And be sure to say hello to our PNWMM Team in the Red Shirts...They work hard so that you can have a Magical Day! And come say hello to me (Don) too! We would love to chat with you!\r\n\r\n<p>We can\'t wait to meet YOU!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you have other questions please email us at info@pnwmousemeet.com</p>','Know Before You Go','','inherit','closed','closed','','659-revision-v1','','','2019-07-23 15:07:15','2019-07-23 15:07:15','',659,'https://pnwmousemeet.com/659-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(874,1,'2019-07-23 15:09:05','2019-07-23 15:09:05','<h3>When to Arrive and Timing of Events</h3>\r\nCheck in begins at 9am. Rope Drop takes place at 10am and our first Guest Speaker begins at 11am. Be sure to arrive early and don’t miss a thing!\r\nDO bring your ID as this is how we will check you in. Bring a smile, camera and a pocket full of Pixie Dust… We will do the rest!\r\n<h3>Food, Snacks, and More!</h3>\r\nThe Lynnwood Convention Center will have three food locations serving Sandwiches, Salads, Pizza, Ice Cream, Popcorn, Mickey Rice Krispy Treats, Coffee, Sodas and so much more. They will even have Mint Juleps with or without a splash of Bourbon! Vegetarian Food options will be available.\r\n<h3>PNWMM Info Booth</h3>\r\nHere you can ask any questions about the event as well as purchase books pertaining to our Author Jeff Kurtti, purchase exclusive Limited Edition PNWMM Pins (new design this year!!), a new PNWMM Print featuring and celebrating the Haunted Mansion’s 50 th , logo mugs, pens and more!\r\n\r\n<a name=\"guest\"></a>\r\n<a name=\"celebrity\"></a>\r\n<h3>Celebrity Meet &amp; Greets</h3>\r\nAll of our Guest Speakers, Jeff Kurtti, Ron Clements and Joe Rohde will be available at various times to meet YOU! Because of high Guest demand to meet Guest Speakers we do have to limit time and items to be signed so that as many Guests can meet them as possible.\r\nThere will be no charge to meet the Guest Speakers or for Autographs.\r\n\r\n<strong>For Joe &amp; Ron</strong>, there is a limit of <strong